    section.section--theories
        .wrap--content

            h2.heading--2.top.
                While the exact cause of binge eating disorder (B.E.D.) is unknown,

            h1.heading--1
                | Research suggests B.E.D. may have a neurobiological basis 
                br.phoneStyle
                | with genetic and environmental risk factors

            h2.heading--2.mobileContspace
                | Prevailing theories that may support a neurobiological basis for !{BED}:

            .row.brain

                .icon.is--vc

                h4.heading--4.mobileHeading--4.distinguishfooter
                    | Reward center and impulsivity dysregulation theory
                    sup 1-4 
                p.mobileP--1
                    | Adults with !{BED} have shown reduced activity in impulse control&ndash;related regions of the brain#[sup 1]

            .row.neuron

                .icon.is--nd

                h4.heading--4.mobileHeading--5.distinguishfooter
                    | Neurotransmitter dysregulation theory
                    sup 5-7
                p.mobileP--2
                    | Dopamine signaling converts sensory stimuli into processes that may generate or enhance &ldquo;wanting&rdquo; of a particular food
                    sup 5,8,9

            .row.neuron-closeup

                .icon.is--vc

                h4.heading--4.mobileHeading--6.distinguishfooter
                    | Endogenous &micro;-opioid signaling dysfunction theory
                    sup 5,10,11
                
                ul.square
                    li.listStyle.limitwidth
                        span
                            | &#956;-Opioid receptor polymorphisms are more often found #[br.desktop-break]
                            | in adults with !{BED}
                            sup 5
                    li.listStyle
                        span
                            | Opioid receptor involvement in reward processing has been demonstrated primarily from animal studies
                            sup 10,11
                //p
