    section.section--factors
        .wrap--content

            h2.heading--2.mobileTitle.
                Research suggests risk factors for !{BED} may include:

            .row.dna

                .icon.is--vc

                h4.heading--4.distinguishfooter Genetic influences
                    sup 5,12,13

                ul.square
                    li.listStyle
                        | !{BED} appears to run in families, which may reflect additive genetic influences
                        sup 12
                    li.listStyle
                        | Genetic differences in neurobiological components of the brain's reward center have been observed
                        sup 5,13

            .row.people

                .icon.is--vc

                h4.heading--4.mobileHeading--7.distinguishfooter Environmental and social influences
                    sup 14,15

                ul.square
                    li.listStyle
                        | In a case-controlled retrospective assessment of 162 women with !{BED}, stressful life events were reported more frequently in the year preceding !{BED} onset than in non-!{BED} controls
                        sup 14
                    li.listStyle
                        | In a nationally representative survey of 5,702 adults, of the men (n=30) and women (n=75) who reported having !{BED}, 98% and 90%, respectively, reported experiencing some form of trauma*
